    "collapsible_content_TPUX4E": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_tab_cCLD8m": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "1. How does a robot vacuum cleaner navigate and plan its path?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Lidar Laser Navigation: The robot vacuum uses Lidar to scan the room and generate a precise floor plan. It efficiently plans a \"bow\" cleaning path for complete coverage.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_QaBBfA": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "2. How strong is the suction power of robot vacuum? Can it thoroughly clean carpets and pet hair?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>The suction power of honiture robotic cleaners <strong>4500pa-5000pa<\/strong>, and the average suction power is higher than the mainstream level. The <strong>honiture v8pro<\/strong> can reach a suction power of <strong>5000pa, <\/strong>which can easily clean pet hair.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_MAGTKA": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "3. Can the robot vacuum avoid obstacles, such as electrical cords, toys, or pet waste?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Yes. <strong>Honiture robot vacuum is equipped with enhanced navigation and obstacle recognition<\/strong>. These technologies can accurately identify small obstacles on the ground, such as wires, slippers, toys, and even pet feces, and intelligently avoid them, greatly reducing the risk of getting stuck or causing secondary contamination.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_KGz8gV": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "4. Can the robot vacuum cross thresholds or carpets?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Yes. Our robot vacuums typically have an obstacle tolerance of<strong> 2 cm <\/strong>and can easily cross common thresholds and carpet edges.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_eftVnN": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "5. How do I perform routine maintenance on my robot vacuum?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<ul><li>Cleaning the Dust Bin: It's recommended to empty the dust bin after each cleaning to maintain optimal suction power.<\/li><li>Cleaning the Filter: It's recommended to clean the filter weekly with a cleaning brush and replace it every <strong>6-12 months<\/strong> to prevent clogging.<\/li><li>Cleaning the Roller and Side Brushes: Regularly check the main and side brushes for tangled hair and clean them with the included cleaning tool.<\/li><li>Wiping the Sensors: Regularly wipe the various sensors on the device with a clean, dry cloth to prevent dust from affecting their accuracy.<\/li><\/ul>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        }
      },
